</node>
<node TEXT="Level" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_216257632" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642">
<node TEXT="Beginner" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_922166206" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642">
<node TEXT="[1/4] 1. Issue" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1521575935" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642">
<node TEXT="B.1.1 What is the main legal question in this scenario?" ID="ID_706068463" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.2 How can the issue be framed as a yes-or-no question?" ID="ID_1133783615" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.3 Why is identifying the issue the first step in legal reasoning?" ID="ID_1981543785" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.4 What facts make this issue legally significant?" ID="ID_1541655730" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.5 What are some common mistakes in stating a legal issue?" ID="ID_1033681345" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.6 How can you distinguish between a factual issue and a legal issue?" ID="ID_969907388" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.7 How does the issue determine the rest of the analysis?" ID="ID_1654908556" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.8 What if the issue was framed more broadly or narrowly—how would that affect your analysis?" ID="ID_1105906935" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.9 How might the tone or language of the issue affect the reader’s perception of importance?" ID="ID_1479768630" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.10 What assumptions are built into how the issue is stated?" ID="ID_1998565501" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.11 How does identifying multiple possible issues affect the structure of your essay?" ID="ID_861904912" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.1.12 What is the relationship between a legal issue and the real-world conflict it represents?" ID="ID_1084252607" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
</node>
<node TEXT="[2/4] 2. Rule" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_379350768" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642">
<node TEXT="B.2.1 What legal rule or principle governs this issue?" ID="ID_60847058" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.2 Where does this rule come from—case law, statute, or another source?" ID="ID_645936864" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.3 How do you summarize the rule without losing key detail?" ID="ID_727754760" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.4 Why is this rule relevant to the issue identified?" ID="ID_1623679049" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.5 What are the elements or conditions of the rule?" ID="ID_1971600598" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.6 How do courts typically interpret this rule?" ID="ID_1140447799" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.7 What if different jurisdictions use different rules—how does that change the analysis?" ID="ID_1952840044" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.8 How would you apply this rule in a different factual context?" ID="ID_1766902964" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.9 How does stating the rule clearly help your audience follow your reasoning?" ID="ID_1219805753" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.10 What tone does a strong rule statement convey—certainty, caution, neutrality?" ID="ID_1204983054" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.11 How does the rule connect to broader principles of justice or policy?" ID="ID_977644159" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.2.12 Why is it important to cite the rule’s source accurately?" ID="ID_992900557" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
</node>
<node TEXT="[3/4] 3. Application" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_411909638" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642">
<node TEXT="B.3.1 How does the rule apply to the specific facts of the case?" ID="ID_43423360" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.2 What factual details are most important in this application?" ID="ID_1080232238" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.3 What steps do you take to connect facts to legal rules?" ID="ID_893894595" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.4 Why is this the most complex part of legal analysis?" ID="ID_1179588041" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.5 What counterarguments could be raised against your application?" ID="ID_406123197" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.6 How do you evaluate the strength of an application argument?" ID="ID_913562539" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.7 What if two interpretations of the same fact lead to different outcomes?" ID="ID_107020789" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.8 How can analogy help clarify your application?" ID="ID_956148112" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.9 What tone or rhetorical strategy helps persuade your reader in this section?" ID="ID_582562882" CREATED="1754240942642" MODIFIED="1754240942642" />
<node TEXT="B.3.10 How might audience expectations shape how you apply the rule?" ID="ID_321647514" CREATED="1754240942643" MODIFIED="1754240942643" />
<node TEXT="B.3.11 How does writing out the application section clarify your own understanding?" ID="ID_881149392" CREATED="1754240942643" MODIFIED="1754240942643" />
<node TEXT="B.3.12 What would happen if this application ignored key facts—how would that affect credibility?" ID="ID_866196415" CREATED="1754240942643" MODIFIED="1754240942643" />
</node>
<node TEXT="[4/4] 4. Conclusion" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1828064299" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471">
<node TEXT="B.4.1 What is the final answer to the legal issue based on your reasoning?" ID="ID_865590321" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.2 How should the conclusion be phrased to clearly reflect your analysis?" ID="ID_152522336" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.3 Why is it important not to introduce new ideas in the conclusion?" ID="ID_1692780683" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.4 What makes a conclusion feel complete or satisfying in legal writing?" ID="ID_1679102345" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.5 How does the conclusion reinforce your rule and application sections?" ID="ID_1639624183" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.6 What are signs that a conclusion may be too vague or unsupported?" ID="ID_159198752" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.7 What if you included a recommendation or next step in the conclusion—would that help or distract?" ID="ID_392180946" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.8 How might the tone of your conclusion affect the reader’s impression of your argument?" ID="ID_1400876518" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.9 How does a well-structured conclusion reflect critical thinking skills?" ID="ID_654873587" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.10 What makes a conclusion legally persuasive as well as logically sound?" ID="ID_830292146" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.11 Why is it useful to revisit the original issue when writing the conclusion?" ID="ID_419027373" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
<node TEXT="B.4.12 How can you revise a weak conclusion to make it stronger and clearer?" ID="ID_532230962" CREATED="1754240942471" MODIFIED="1754240942471" />
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Intermediate" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_238564525" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355">
<node TEXT="[1/4] 1. Issue" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1745756107" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355">
<node TEXT="I.1.1 How do you differentiate between primary and secondary legal issues in a complex case?" ID="ID_282566364" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.2 Why is precise framing of the issue critical for effective legal analysis?" ID="ID_1354175659" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.3 How can multiple issues interact or conflict within a single case?" ID="ID_1866731925" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.4 What strategies help in narrowing a broad legal issue to a manageable question?" ID="ID_1301839817" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.5 How does the context or background influence the way the issue is framed?" ID="ID_1075833834" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.6 What if an issue is ambiguous—how can you clarify or redefine it for stronger analysis?" ID="ID_442809723" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.7 How does the issue relate to the underlying facts and legal principles involved?" ID="ID_1079066255" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.8 How might different stakeholders perceive the issue differently?" ID="ID_1091191001" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.9 What impact does the wording of the issue have on the audience’s understanding or bias?" ID="ID_1589266220" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.10 How can you use framing to highlight the significance of an issue in your argument?" ID="ID_1237568050" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.11 What role does critical questioning play in refining the legal issue?" ID="ID_1551828570" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.1.12 How can framing affect the logical flow of your entire IRAC analysis?" ID="ID_1935074052" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
</node>
<node TEXT="[2/4] 2. Rule" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1340608312" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355">
<node TEXT="I.2.1 How do you evaluate the relevance and authority of different legal rules for your issue?" ID="ID_1316724634" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.2 Why might conflicting rules or precedents exist, and how should they be handled?" ID="ID_149774923" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.3 How can you synthesize multiple related rules into a coherent statement?" ID="ID_1672615724" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.4 What criteria determine the priority of one rule over another in legal reasoning?" ID="ID_1926518768" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.5 How does statutory interpretation influence the application of rules?" ID="ID_1086606594" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.6 What role do legal maxims or principles play in shaping rules?" ID="ID_304347325" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.7 How do you identify exceptions or limitations within a legal rule?" ID="ID_692639593" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.8 What if a rule has evolved over time—how does historical context affect its current meaning?" ID="ID_1057145294" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.9 How can analogies to other legal areas clarify the application of a rule?" ID="ID_1850906302" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.10 How does precision in stating the rule affect the strength of your argument?" ID="ID_1110768351" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.11 What tone should be adopted when presenting rules to convey objectivity and authority?" ID="ID_1134178118" CREATED="1754240942355" MODIFIED="1754240942355" />
<node TEXT="I.2.12 How does understanding the rule’s purpose or policy enhance legal analysis?" ID="ID_927005694" CREATED="1754240942356" MODIFIED="1754240942356" />
</node>
<node TEXT="[3/4] 3. Application" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1917109601" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242">
<node TEXT="I.3.1 How do you critically analyze facts to determine their relevance under the rule?" ID="ID_1458370628" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242" />
<node TEXT="I.3.2 What methods help identify strengths and weaknesses in your application?" ID="ID_650583752" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242" />
<node TEXT="I.3.3 How can you balance competing interpretations of facts in your analysis?" ID="ID_1486904534" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242" />
<node TEXT="I.3.4 Why is it important to consider alternative applications of the rule?" ID="ID_155193381" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242" />
<node TEXT="I.3.5 How does the application demonstrate logical coherence between facts and rule?" ID="ID_1652227129" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242" />
<node TEXT="I.3.6 What role does precedent play in strengthening your application?" ID="ID_868348242" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242" />
<node TEXT="I.3.7 How can hypothetical scenarios deepen understanding in the application stage?" ID="ID_596267816" CREATED="1754240942242" MODIFIED="1754240942242" />
<node TEXT="I.3.8 What if new evidence contradicted your application—how would you revise your analysis?" ID="ID_493192447" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.3.9 How can tone and rhetoric be used ethically to persuade in this section?" ID="ID_35910945" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.3.10 In what ways do audience assumptions influence your application arguments?" ID="ID_1286292998" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.3.11 How does the application phase help you develop critical thinking skills?" ID="ID_1628005946" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.3.12 What are the risks of overgeneralizing facts in your application?" ID="ID_1717551112" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
</node>
<node TEXT="[4/4] 4. Conclusion" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_425479113" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243">
<node TEXT="I.4.1 How can you formulate a conclusion that logically follows from your application?" ID="ID_614452221" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.4.2 What techniques ensure your conclusion addresses the original issue fully?" ID="ID_1385912184" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.4.3 Why should the conclusion avoid introducing new arguments or evidence?" ID="ID_860438833" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.4.4 How does the conclusion contribute to the persuasiveness of your legal analysis?" ID="ID_808140610" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.4.5 What if your conclusion acknowledges uncertainty or alternative outcomes—how does that affect credibility?" ID="ID_1231240098" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.4.6 How can revisiting the issue in your conclusion reinforce your argument’s coherence?" ID="ID_33712404" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.4.7 What tone best suits a conclusion aiming for professional and objective impact?" ID="ID_140028516" CREATED="1754240942243" MODIFIED="1754240942243" />
<node TEXT="I.4.8 How can you use your conclusion to suggest implications or recommendations responsibly?" ID="ID_558150128" CREATED="1754240942244" MODIFIED="1754240942244" />
<node TEXT="I.4.9 How does clarity in your conclusion reflect mastery of the IRAC method?" ID="ID_456315745" CREATED="1754240942244" MODIFIED="1754240942244" />
